<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870519-0150 </DOCNO><HL> Letters to the Editor:Go Directly to College</HL><DD> 05/19/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><TEXT>   I want to note another way of sending the kids to college with &quot;financial aid&quot; (second front, April 30). That is, get a divorce in Indiana, and have a judge order child support that includes paying college tuition and expenses. Judges in Indiana have the right to order divorced fathers to pay full costs of college, under penalty of a felony conviction and contempt of court. According to some judges, designer jeans, designer shoes and cars also are mandated for college, and the father must pay or go to jail.    Dick Livingston   Kokomo, Ind.</TEXT></DOC>